  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Synergies of ESD and GCE in Pacific Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While there is no universal model of education for sustainable development, the goal emphasis and process must therefore locally define its own priorities and actions. In the Small Island Developing States (SIDS) of the South Pacific, sustainability is a complex goal that requires multidisciplinary strategies taking into account social, cultural, ecological and economic factors. Given the size of these island nations, actions could be better taken in a collaborative manner where possible for better synergies. Educational institutions at all levels have important roles in bringing understanding of threats to sustainability and in devising strategies using an inclusive approach in collaboration with the members of each community to address these threats.</narrative>
  </description>
